@{
    ViewBag.Title = "Text";
}

<script type="text/javascript" src="~/dist/MyApp/Scripts/FormBinding_Text.js"></script>

<div class="page-header">
    <h1>Testing text input bindings</h1>
</div>
<div class="container-fluid">
    <div class="form-horizontal">
        <div class="form-group">
            <label for="title" class="control-label col-sm-4">Title</label>
            <div class="col-sm-8">
                <input id="title" type="text" class="form-control" />
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="form-group">
            <label for="content" class="control-label col-sm-4">Content</label>
            <div class="col-sm-8">
                <textarea id="content" class="form-control" rows="6"></textarea>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <hr />
    <h2>Here is the preview</h2>
    <hr />
    <h3>Put title here</h3>
    <div>Put body here</div>
</div>
@*
1. Create an app object with title and body observable properties, give them some initial values
2. Bind these properties to input#title and textarea#content
Keep in mind to use the preferred binding, with real-time update
3. Then bind the observables to the preview area (h3 and div)
4. Test everyting
5. Add the conversion of \n into <br/> from textarea using a read-only computed observable
Remember that there can be multiple new lines.
6. Test everything
*@